<br>
I get a KEI and chain 51 earth pets exclusively, forego the burnout and give them only a DS.  No nukage.  I have absolutely no downtime unless I screw up and have to zone or need to get KEI refreshed<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Just make sure to get your 5 pts of damage in (I just use burst of flame to pull).<br>
<br>
Because the lvl 1 nuke is not line of sight, the easiest thing to do is target a prisoner, run almost all the way back to where you have your pet parked (should be at or near the zone line), nuke and wait.  I usually park my pet in one of the corners of the horse shoe leading to the zone-out hall as opposed to right at the zone.<br>
<br>
Warnings:  <br>
The Iksar monk is a nasty critter.  He chews through about 5 pets.  I would consider myslef to be reasonably decent at chaining and it takes me 15-25% of my mana bar to kill this guy.  Until you get the spawn timing down, I would recommend checking frequently to be sure he has not popped as he WILL assist anything you pull.  Also, try and land a malosi on this guy.  Without it I've noticed my dirtball's root has a tendency not to stick when I really need it to.  With malosi I've yet to not have it stick.<br>
<br>
The sentries (at least on the Zeb server) are SERIOUSLY bugged.  Nine times out of 10 they run a couple laps around the prison before warping right on top of you.  One or two times out of ten they will bring rats with them when they warp.  The sentries WILL assist prisoners as well if you pull a prisoner with a sentry in the vicinity.  Easiest way to pull these guys is nuke them, run back to your pet and just stand there until the sentry warps onto you.  You'll get hit a couple times, but you'll live I promise.  They hit for 136 max.  Let your pet take over from there.  Again, try and land a malosi on these guys.<br>
<br>
Rats are not a problem if you are careful.  If you use the pulling technique I described above you should have no problem with the prisoners hitting you before you get back and gaining pet aggro.  Bottom line is this:  DO NOT let your pet fight prisoners more than halfway down the horse shoe.  As long as you keep it near the zone, you'll be fine.<br>
<br>
